The article is a Presidential Memorandum issued on January 15, 2019, regarding the delegation of functions and authorities under the Hizballah International Financing Prevention Act of 2015 and its amendments. The memorandum delegates certain functions and authorities to the Secretary of State, the Secretary of the Treasury, and the Director of National Intelligence. The delegated functions and authorities are to be exercised in coordination with other departments and agencies through the National Security Presidential Memorandum-4 process. This memorandum rescinds and replaces any prior delegations of authority under the Hizballah International Financing Prevention Act. The Secretary of State is authorized and directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.